SUMMARY:Evansburg Park
DESCRIPTION:Walking Tails\nThis walk goes out to the northeast about 1.25 
 miles and then we come back the way we came\, for a total of 2.5 miles. Th
 e trail is a paved surface and fairly shady.\n\nWe will be meeting at the 
 parking lot between the ranger's station and the playground\, near the swi
 ngs.\nCLICK DIRECTLY ON THE MAP IF YOU THINK YOU ARE LOST. IT WILL BRING Y
 OU RIGHT TO US WHERE WE MEET.\n\nStart Time: We will start hiking promptly
  at the scheduled time.\n\nDuration of the walk – depends on the people 
 and dogs in the group. We frequently end up walking in smaller packs based
  on the comfort level of the participants.\n\nIn the past this walk takes 
 about 1 hour\, and longer for time spent in the open fields.\n\nPlease rem
 ember pooh bags and that your dog must be on a leash that is no more than 
 10 feet long.\n\nNOTICE: By attending this event you are agreeing that YOU
  ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR YOUR OWN SAFETY AT ALL TIMES. The hike leader and oth
 er members cannot be held responsible for any damages\, accidents\, or lia
 bilities incurred while hiking with us.\n\nEvansburg State Park Map (http:
 //www.dcnr.state.pa.us/cs/groups/public/documents/document/dcnr_004726.pdf
 )
